{"type": "user", "message": {"role": "user", "content": [{"tool_use_id": "chatcmpl-tool-bcbc47abf5b886f9", "type": "tool_result", "content": "# On the Emotion Understanding of Synthesized Speech\narXiv: 2603.16483\nAuthors: Yuan Ge, Haishu Zhao, Aokai Hao, Junxiang Zhang, Bei Li, Xiaoqian Liu, Chenglong Wang, Jianjin Wang, Bingsen Zhou, Bingyu Liu, Jingbo Zhu, Zhengtao Yu, Tong Xiao\nYear: 2026 | Venue: \nTopic: speech_other\nStatus: unread\n\nContributions:\n  1. Discriminative Speech Emotion Recognition (SER) models generalize poorly to synthesized speech, exhibiting a clear performance gap compared to human speech.\n  2. The dominant source of the synthesized domain shift is the speech token prediction stage, whereas subsequent flow matching and vocoder stages contribute substantially less.\n  3. Supervised and domain-adversarial fine-tuning fail to fundamentally resolve the generalization gap, indicating that existing SER models rely on non-robust shortcuts rather than capturing fundamental features.\n  4. Generative Speech Language Models tend to infer emotion primarily from textual semantics while ignoring paralinguistic cues, a behavior that persists even with prompt engineering.\n\nTags: Eval, Eval/听觉感知, LALM, TTS", "is_error": false}]}, "parent_tool_use_id": null, "session_id": "24c82511-d1b1-4979-9700-c1b74193babb", "uuid": "5f468a7e-a360-441b-9c2b-2ad2788e7b2e", "timestamp": "2026-07-21T11:33:41.639Z", "tool_use_result": {"stdout": "# On the Emotion Understanding of Synthesized Speech\narXiv: 2603.16483\nAuthors: Yuan Ge, Haishu Zhao, Aokai Hao, Junxiang Zhang, Bei Li, Xiaoqian Liu, Chenglong Wang, Jianjin Wang, Bingsen Zhou, Bingyu Liu, Jingbo Zhu, Zhengtao Yu, Tong Xiao\nYear: 2026 | Venue: \nTopic: speech_other\nStatus: unread\n\nContributions:\n  1. Discriminative Speech Emotion Recognition (SER) models generalize poorly to synthesized speech, exhibiting a clear performance gap compared to human speech.\n  2. The dominant source of the synthesized domain shift is the speech token prediction stage, whereas subsequent flow matching and vocoder stages contribute substantially less.\n  3. Supervised and domain-adversarial fine-tuning fail to fundamentally resolve the generalization gap, indicating that existing SER models rely on non-robust shortcuts rather than capturing fundamental features.\n  4. Generative Speech Language Models tend to infer emotion primarily from textual semantics while ignoring paralinguistic cues, a behavior that persists even with prompt engineering.\n\nTags: Eval, Eval/听觉感知, LALM, TTS", "stderr": "", "interrupted": false, "isImage": false, "noOutputExpected": false}}
{"type": "user", "message": {"role": "user", "content": [{"tool_use_id": "chatcmpl-tool-85541a29ce655a36", "type": "tool_result", "content": "# StyleStream: Real-Time Zero-Shot Voice Style Conversion\narXiv: 2602.20113\nAuthors: Yisi Liu, Nicholas Lee, Gopala Anumanchipalli\nYear: 2026 | Venue: \nTopic: tts_vc\nStatus: unread\n\nContributions:\n  1. We introduce StyleStream, the first real-time voice style conversion system with an end-to-end latency of 1 second.\n  2. By combining ASR loss and a compact quantization codebook, the Destylizer achieves cleaner content-style disentanglement compared to existing methods.\n  3. Trained on 50k hours of English data, StyleStream delivers state-of-the-art conversion quality, substantially improving accent and emotion similarity over prior work.\n\nTags: TTS, TTS/控制-风格标签, TTS/功能-流式", "is_error": false}]}, "parent_tool_use_id": null, "session_id": "24c82511-d1b1-4979-9700-c1b74193babb", "uuid": "b5454cf7-54a8-4928-a2ba-929e3fdd68bc", "timestamp": "2026-07-21T11:33:41.874Z", "tool_use_result": {"stdout": "# StyleStream: Real-Time Zero-Shot Voice Style Conversion\narXiv: 2602.20113\nAuthors: Yisi Liu, Nicholas Lee, Gopala Anumanchipalli\nYear: 2026 | Venue: \nTopic: tts_vc\nStatus: unread\n\nContributions:\n  1. We introduce StyleStream, the first real-time voice style conversion system with an end-to-end latency of 1 second.\n  2. By combining ASR loss and a compact quantization codebook, the Destylizer achieves cleaner content-style disentanglement compared to existing methods.\n  3. Trained on 50k hours of English data, StyleStream delivers state-of-the-art conversion quality, substantially improving accent and emotion similarity over prior work.\n\nTags: TTS, TTS/控制-风格标签, TTS/功能-流式", "stderr": "", "interrupted": false, "isImage": false, "noOutputExpected": false}}
